This paper deals with the study of natural strategy elimination procedures for strategic games, which is a topic in game theory. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also discusses the notion of rationalizability, which is related to decision-making and could fall under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of reduction relations and parametrized systems of beliefs, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
